Modifications by Colin (@cejor6) (https://github.com/cejor6) include:
  - Replaced the single global tool mutex with a MutexRegistry that hands
    out per-page mutexes plus a global "exclusive" mode for topology
    operations. Page-scoped tools acting on different pages now run
    concurrently when --experimentalPageIdRouting is enabled.
  - Added a Streamable HTTP transport (alongside stdio) that supports
    multiple concurrent MCP client sessions sharing one Chrome browser,
    with optional bearer-token authentication and host validation.
  - Extracted shared state (browser/context lifecycle + MutexRegistry)
    from createMcpServer so multiple McpServer instances can share one
    browser.

